Arapuke Enduro
Entries are open for the Arapuke Enduro!!! This year we're part of the Wellington Enduro Series and this is a race you do not want to miss!

Everyone is welcome whether it’s your first Enduro or you are riding to be the MMBC Club Champ (just remember – only MMBC members who ride the hard course will be in the running for the Club Enduro Champ title).

Not sure how an Enduro works or a bit tentative to enter a race? We’ve got you covered. Join the gang at the back of the pack and take all the time you need. A tail-end Charlie will sweep down and make sure no one overtakes you.

Want to participate as a Minder Rider for your child on the course? That’s cool. There is no cost to do that. Just choose “minder rider” when you enter. This option is only available for the Intermediate course.

The Intermediate course will have four stages of downhill fun. Be prepared for mostly Grade 3. There may be a Grade 4 thrown in but everything is rollable. Ready to send it on harder stuff? Then the Hard course is for you. It will have five stages of Grade 3, 4, 5 and 6 trails. It will be hard.

You can change your course choice on race day! Heaps more information at mmbc.co.nz/event/mmbc-club-enduro/

